---
import PageMeta from "../components/PageMeta.astro";
import PageLayout from "../layouts/PageLayout.astro";
import { SITE_TITLE } from "../config";
---

<PageLayout>
  <PageMeta title={`AI | ${SITE_TITLE}`} slot="meta" />
  <Fragment slot="main">
    <section class="mb-8">
      <h1 class="font-extrabold text-5xl md:text-6xl tracking-tight pt-4 pb-8 overflow-hidden">
        <span class="bg-gradient-to-br from-[#fb923c] via-[#f97316] to-[#ea580c] dark:from-primary-main dark:via-primary-main dark:to-primary-main bg-clip-text text-transparent">
          AI
        </span>
      </h1>

      <div class="space-y-6 prose max-w-none prose-sleek">
        <p>
          This page describes how I use artificial intelligence on this site and in my work.
        </p>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-text-bold">Content authorship</h2>
          <p>
            All articles, blog posts, and opinions on this site are written by me, Simon Pamies.
            The ideas, positions, and arguments are my own, shaped by experience shipping production systems
            in cloud architecture, AI/ML, and enterprise software.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-text-bold">How I use AI tools</h2>
          <p>
            I use AI tools as part of my workflow. Specifically:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Writing assistance:</strong> I may use LLMs to help with grammar, phrasing, and structure. The substance and direction of every piece is mine.</li>
            <li><strong>Code:</strong> I use AI-assisted coding tools for development tasks like refactoring, boilerplate, and exploration. All code is reviewed and understood before it ships.</li>
            <li><strong>Research:</strong> I use AI tools to search, summarize, and cross-reference sources. I verify claims before publishing.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-text-bold">What I don't do</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>I don't publish AI-generated content without substantial human review and editing.</li>
            <li>I don't use AI to fabricate quotes, data, or sources.</li>
            <li>I don't use AI to generate opinions I don't hold.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-text-bold">My position</h2>
          <p>
            AI is a tool. Like any tool, its value depends on how it's used. I believe in transparency about AI usage,
            human oversight at every decision point, and the principle that the person publishing carries responsibility
            for what they publish — regardless of which tools helped produce it.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </Fragment>
</PageLayout>
